  "prompt": "How much does it cost to attend a TED talk?",
  "response": "The cost to attend a TED talk can vary significantly depending on the type of event and location. For the flagship TED Conference, ticket prices are often several thousand dollars, ranging from $5,000 to $25,000 or more. These prices reflect the premium experience and access to a wide range of activities and networking opportunities.\n\nFor smaller, independently organized TEDx events, the prices can be much lower, sometimes ranging from free to a few hundred dollars depending on the event's scale and location.\n\nIt's best to check the specific event's website for the most accurate and up-to-date information on ticket prices.",
